  <description type="morphology">Perennials, 10–30(–40+) cm (caudices often woody). Cauline leaves mostly crowded over proximal 1/4(–1/2) of plant heights, internodes mostly 1–5(–35 mm); lobes mostly oblanceolate to linear, (5–)10–35(–45+) × (1–)2–3(–5) mm. Calyculi of 7–9 deltate to lance-linear bractlets 2–4+ mm. Ray florets 0, or 8; laminae yellow, (6–)12–20+ mm. Disc corollas yellow, sometimes with red-brown nerves, throats equal to or longer than lobes. Cypselae 5–7 mm; pappi usually 0, rarely 0.1–0.5 mm. 2n = 22, 24.</description>
